# Long-Running Task Harness

Patterns from [Anthropic's long-running agent harness research](https://www.anthropic.com/engineering/effective-harnesses-for-long-running-agents) to prevent context loss, premature completion, and undocumented state.

## Bootstrap sequence

Every new session or subagent working on an existing plan must start with:

1. Read the plan file — understand scope and current todo statuses
2. Read the progress file (if it exists) — see what was built and what interfaces exist
3. Run `bun run typecheck` — verify the codebase is clean before writing code
4. Identify the next incomplete todo — do NOT re-derive priorities from scratch

## Progress file

For plans with 10+ todos, maintain a progress file at `docs/progress/<plan-name>.md`.

- **Created** after the first layer completes, listing contracts/types established
- **Updated** after each todo completes: what was built, what it exports, any decisions made
- **Read first** by every subsequent session or subagent to avoid re-exploring the codebase

```
## Completed
- [types] EvalTask, GraderResult defined in src/evals/types.ts
- [code-grader-quick-scan] gradeQuickScan() in src/evals/graders/code-graders.ts

## Current layer: L3
## Next todo: llm-grader-quick-scan

## Decisions
- Used Zod discriminated union for GraderResult (pass/fail/skip)
- LLM grader prompts import from momentum-rubric.ts, not inline text
```

## Verification gate

A todo is NOT complete until all of these pass:

1. `bun run typecheck` passes
2. `bun test` passes (if tests exist for this module)
3. `bun run lint` passes
4. The progress file is updated
5. A git commit is made

Do NOT mark a todo complete based on "it looks right." Run the checks.

## Incremental commits

Commit after each todo, not after each layer. Format: `<scope>: <todo-id> — <what was done>`. This provides recovery points if a later todo breaks something.

## Premature completion prevention

- Do NOT declare the plan "done" until every todo is marked complete
- After the final todo, run the full verification suite one more time
- If any todo was skipped or deferred, note why in the progress file and inform the user
- Do NOT look around, see progress, and declare victory — check the todo list

Plans under 10 todos don't need a progress file, but still require the verification gate.
